nd the neat way I got out of it?' said the actor mellowly. 'Endless ovations,' said the black-eyed lady, 'they gave me such ovations as I shall never forget....' In this way they interrupted one another, each with his or her own recollections, and the man in the pale pants for the third time asked a musing Luzhin for 'one small cigarette.' He was a beginning poet and read his poems with fervor, with a singsong lilt, slightly jerking his head and looking into space. Normally he held his head high